var notificationContent = {
	"egmcovid19":"<b>#LEGALUPDATE #MCA #08APRIL2020 #CIRCULAR #EGM #COVID19</b><br/>Due to the pandemic caused by COVID-19, Companies are requested to take all urgent business, other than ordinary business or business where the person has right to be heard, which require the approval of members, through the postal ballot/e-voting without holding a physical general meeting. In case of unavoidable circumstances, Companies are allowed to conduct EGMs on or before June 30, 2020, through VC or OAVM along with the facility of e-voting (if required) after complying the prescribed procedure and all the resolutions related thereto shall be filed with Registrar of Companies within 60 days.</br>For More Information:-</br><a href=\"http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Circular14_08042020.pdf\">http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Circular14_08042020.pdf</a><br/><br/>",
	"cfss2020":"<b>#LEGALUPDATE #MCA #30MARCH2020 #CompaniesFreshStartScheme2020 #CFSS2020 #COVID19</b><br/>The Companies Fresh Start Scheme, 2020 (CFSS-2020) shall come into force on the April 01, 2020 and shall remain in force till September 30, 2020.<br/>Every Defaulting Company shall be required to pay normal fees as on the date of filing of each belated document and no additional fees shall be payable.<br/>This CFSS is applicable on below mentioned forms: - <br/>1. AOC-4 (Financial Statements) <br/>2. MGT-7 (Annual return) <br/>3. Others E-forms required to be filed with RoC<br/>This CFSS is not applicable on below mentioned forms: - <br/>1. SH-7 (increase in authorised capital) <br/>2. All charge related forms (CHG-1, CHG-4, CHG-8 and CHG-9).</br>For More Information:-</br><a href=\"http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Circular12_30032020.pdf\">http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Circular12_30032020.pdf</a><br/><br/>",
	"llpss":"<b>#LEGALUPDATE #MCA #30MARCH2020 #LLPSettlementScheme2020 #Modification #COVID19</b><br/>The Scheme shall come into force on the April 01, 2020 and shall remain in force till September 30, 2020. <br/>Any Defaulting LLP is permitted to file belated document which were due for filing till August 31, 2020 and no additional fees shall be payable.<br/>The defaulting LLPs which have filed their belated documents till September 30, 2020 and made good the default, shall not be subjected to prosecution by the Registrar for such defaults. <br/>Exception: - <br/>This scheme shall not applicable for LLPs which have made an application in Form 24 LLP for strike-off. <br/>For More Information:-</br><a href=\"http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Circular13_30032020.pdf\">http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Circular13_30032020.pdf</a><br/><br/>",
	"covid19special":"<b>#LEGALUPDATE #MCA #24MARCH2020 #Special Measures under Companies Act, 2013 (CA-2013) and Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 in view of COVID-19 outbreak</b><br/>MCA has decided to provide the following relaxations to the Companies:</br>1.There will be no additional fees for late filing of e-forms From April 01, 2020, till September 30, 2020;</br>2.The Maximum gap for holding of board meetings in the next two quarters shall be of 180 days instead of 120 days between two consecutive meetings;</br>3.Companies (Auditor’s Report) Order, 2020 will be applicable from FY 2020-21;</br>4.There will be no non-compliance if no meeting of Independent Directors held during the FY 2019-20;</br>5.Companies which are required to create Deposit Repayment Reserve may create such reserve up to June 30, 2020, instead of April 30, 2020;</br>6.The requirement to invest 15% of debentures maturing during a particular year in specified instruments before April 30, 2020, maybe done so before June 30, 2020;</br>7.Newly incorporated Companies need to obtained Certificate of Commencement of Business within 12 months from the date of their incorporation instead of 6 months;</br>8.Non-Compliance of minimum residency for a minimum period of 182 days by at least one director of a Company shall not be treated as non-compliance of Section 149.</br>For More Information:-</br><a href=\"http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Circular_25032020.pdf\">http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Circular_25032020.pdf</a><br/><br/>",
	"covid19caro":"<b>#LEGALUPDATE #MCA #24MARCH2020 #ORDER #CARO #COVID19</b><br/>The Companies in which CARO is applicable shall include in their Auditor’s Report the matters specified in the amended order dated February 25, 2020 for the financial years commencing on or after April 01, 2010 instead of April 01, 2019 as mentioned earlier due to COVID19.</br>For More Information:-</br><a href=\"http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Notification_25032020.pdf\">http://www.mca.gov.in/Ministry/pdf/Notification_25032020.pdf</a><br/><br/>",
